TRUSTABLE-SOFTWARE: This
release of JSON-Library
also referred in the
documentation as nlohmann/json
library is Trustable.

TT-EXPECTATIONS: Documentation
is provided within eclipse-score/inc_nlohmann_json,
specifying what the nlohmann/json
library is expected to
do, and what it must
not do, and how this
is verified.

WFJ-04: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library checks the well-formedness
of array.

NJF-05: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library accepts and rejects
arrays according to RFC8259
ยง5.

NJF-05.1: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library accepts the empty
array.

NJF-05.2: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library accepts the non-empty
arrays.

NJF-05.3: If every value
candidate of a properly
bounded array is accepted
as singleton, then the
service provided by the
nlohmann/json library
accepts the array.

NJF-05.4: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
any improperly bounded
arrays.

NJF-05.5: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
arrays with improper
values.

NJF-05.6: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library accepts nested
arrays.

NJF-05.6.0: The acceptance
of nested arrays by the
service provided by the
nlohmann/json library
does not depend on the
depth of nesting.

NJF-05.7: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does only accept
comma as value separator.

TA-BEHAVIOURS: Expected
or required behaviours
for the nlohmann/json
library are identified,
specified, verified and
validated based on analysis.
